    <briefdescription>
<para>A class which implements a partial derivative operator using a finite differences calculation of order two. A decentered scheme is used at the boundary, whereas centred finite difference are used inside the domain. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>IdxRangeFull</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The index range of the field on which the operator acts (with all dimensions, batched and dimension of interest). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>DerivativeDimension</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The dimension on which the partial derivative is calculated. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
